Imbued with excess and pain, the imagination of the dark mechanics forged the Rapture class Heavy Stalker.
Hunters of titans, they bound and leap across the battlefield after their prey.

This kit includes everything you need to build a Rapture Heavy Stalker in 8mm or AT scale.
The main body measures about the height of the standard Heavy Stalker with the tail adding extra height.
This can be built in any number of ways, the kit is extremely flexible.

The kit includes, amongst standard components:
- 3 different heads, with and without tentacles
- 2 tail poses
- 2 different tail weapons
- 2 different arm weapons

Four files include:
1. Components: individual components to print and pose as you desire. Includes the supported folder.
2. Poses: a number of arms and leg poses to make assembly quicker. Supported versions included.
3. Complete: some example builds which you can use as an example or print as a single object. Supported versions included.

The model has been made to go on a 60mm bases and this has been included.


All files come supported and unsupported.

Pictures of models are test prints.

Note: This is an upgrade package to Quixote-class mechs and similar types of chassis (Imperial Warrior, Etc.)

The Quixote Mech is sold separately here.

Use LOWKEY20 for 20% off your entire purchase, or join my Patreon for 50% off ( www.patreon.com/johnbearross )

---------------------------------------------------------

 The Tortuga Group, a heretofore relatively unknown defense contractor, recently unveiled an upgrade suite for the venerable Quixote-class mech chassis.

 Their Quixote Defense Upgrade Package is a long-distance take on the concept of mechanized walker warfare, with an emphasis on stand-off weaponry and heavy shielding. This may not be suited for the mechanized arenas of Junctionworld, but mercenaries on the open battlefields found throughout the worldgate networks are sure to benefit.

 The new Spina Mk.II C-Beam Cannon is devastatingly effective on distance targets, with the damage inflicted usually an inverse to the target’s proximity.

 For closer adversaries that slip past the C-Beamer, a Redmaw Persecutor-class Plasma Cannon dispenses superheated damage, though its recharge rate has caught some pilots short. Thus, a heavy flamethrower is also added to the Spina Mk.II for supplemental in-close coverage.

 Adding to the new upgrade’s enhancements is the Testudo VI Force Field projector, a variation on shielding systems found on heavier kaiju-fighting megamechs and titans. When properly modulated, this generator can be used to deflect heavy incoming fire, or lend its protection to nearby units.

---------------------------------------------

This kit includes...

1 Plasma Cannon with two optional barrels.
1 C-Beamer Cannon with Auxiliary Flamethrower
2nd Generation Weapon Arms and Upper Arms with support rims to add stability.
1 Force Field Generator with two options of flat magnetized mount or a peg compatible with Imperial Warrior and similar builds.

Enjoy!

Best,
John Bear Ross

Again, that checkout code is LOWKEY20
Thanks!

When da Big Meks gettin' tired of walkin’ up to da enemy just to hit 'em, they built Shoota Botz – walkin’ fortress o’ dakka designed to turn battlefields into bullet storms wiff blasta beams n rokkits. Bristlin' with barrels, belchin' smoke, and covered in rivets, dis bot’s idea of a good time is shootin’ everything that moves... and then shootin’ it again, just to be sure.

From rokkits to rattlin’ big shootas or ork tek blastas, Shoota Botz got more guns than sense – which is just how da greenskins lovin' it. No choppy arms here, just pure ranged firepower, rainin’ lead from across da field while laughin’ like a mad git.

Note: Dis is a fan-made model, full of grimy character and orkiness, but not linked to any official game or company. It’s just for da ladz who like loud machines an’ big fights.

This model is compatible to the bitz of following models:
- Mosha Bot
- Brawla Bot


======= PRINTING =========

- Layer hight 0.05mm
- Use tree / organic supports.
- I printed my test prints with a 0.25mm nozzle (for best quality)
- Orientate the Exhausts01-04 vertical

======= Assembly =========

If you need instructions - just open all files in 3D Builder or e.g. Meshmixer at the same time (drag and drop). There you can have a look where they need to go in 3D.



---
Shame less beggin' for some coins for caffeine I need doin' stuff like that :-)

Please consider a tip ....this highly detailed model was a work of hundeds of hours of free time!
If you do so, I HIGHLY APPRECIATE YOUR GENEROSITY :-)

Kind regands,
Tersus

If it ain’t screamin’, explodin’, or bein’ torn in half, Mosha Bot ain’t interested. Cooked up in the noisy, smoke-filled workshops of the biggest meks, dis beast was built for one thing: gettin’ stuck in and krumpin’ everythin’ wiv brutal enthusiasm.

Loaded with buzzin’ saws, power klaws, and more spiky bitz than a squig’s birthday party, Mosha Bot doesn’t do “subtle.” No guns, no dakka – just pure, up-close smashy business. It stomps straight into the fight, rippin’ tanks in half and makin’ a proper mess of any poor git that gets too close.

Note: Dis is a fan-made model, full of grimy character and orkiness, but not linked to any official game or company. It’s just for da ladz who like loud machines an’ big fights.


This model is compatible to the bitz of following models:
- Shoota Bot
- Brawla Bot


======= PRINTING =========

- Layer hight 0.05mm
- Use tree / organic supports.
- I printed my test prints with a 0.25mm nozzle (for best quality)
- Orientate the Exhausts01-04 vertical

======= Assembly =========

If you need instructions - just open all files in 3D Builder or e.g. Meshmixer at the same time (drag and drop). There you can have a look where they need to go in 3D.



---

If you do so, I HIGHLY APPRECIATE YOUR GENEROSITY :-)

Tersus

‘Isurus pattern’ Dire Wolf Titan armour, Loyalist allegiance, made to fit the LI/Adeptus Titanicus Dire Wolf Titan.

This is a full set of armour plates, to give your Dire Wolf titans a whole new look.

Are you a follower of the Warmaster? Then you’ll want the traitor version here:
https://cults3d.com/:2909778

Looking for a version with a plain, unaligned trim? Then go here:
https://cults3d.com/:2909807

This is a complete kit, replacing all of the armour plates.
Please note that, to utilise the carapace plate(s), you will need to cut GW part 21, just behind the vent, to remove the original carapace plate from the rest of this part before assembling the titan skeleton. Rest assured, it's a very simple cut - see the final photos for reference.

Included are 2 versions of the carapace, split and unsplit. The file '...unsplit' is the carapace in a single piece. The 3-part version is made up of 2 files, '...side' (which you copy and mirror) and '...top'.
The finished carapaces are exactly the same. Printing is faster with the split version (not so tall on the build plate) and tends to give a better surface finish (orientation to build plate). The unsplit version takes longer but, as it's a single piece, is much more robust and easier to swap in and out on your titan.

Most parts feature magnet holes, for either 2mm dia or 5x2x0.5mm magnets, giving the option of painting multiple versions for parts that you can swap in and out. Many can grip to the titan frame without the need for magnets (thigh plate and unsplit carapace feature holes, but you may well find you don't really need them. Shoulder plates on the other hand would need magnetising to be swappable). You'll need to add the appropriate reciprocal magnet holes/magnets to your titan skeleton to make use of these.

Files included: STL, pre-supported STL and Lychee scenes of each part (in the ZIP file) - should you want/need to tweak the supports for your particular printer.

Notes:
This is for the 8mm, AT2018/LI version only and is scaled appropriately for this size.
STLs and supported STLs are for left side versions only of the engine cover, shoulder, shin and thigh plates. These should be copied and mirrored to produce the right side plates (Shin plate is symmetrical, so can just copied), when printing your full set - though the '...full set' Lychee scene included in the ZIP file has this already set up for you. This full set scene utilises the 3-part version of the carapace, so swap these out for the 'unsplit' carapace if you want to print the single piece version with the rest of the parts.

Justification du tag SUP :

STLs and supported STLs are for left side versions only of the engine cover, shoulder, shin and thigh plates. These should be copied and mirrored to produce the right side plates (Shin plate is symmetrical, so can just copied), when printing your full set - though the ‘…full set’ Lychee scene included in the ZIP file has this already set up for you. This full set scene utilises the 3-part version of the carapace, so swap these out for the ‘unsplit’ carapace if you want to print the single piece version with the rest of the parts.

The war for Renner’s World is not going well for the embattled forces defending their home from the invading Kaiju. The abominable walking mega-fauna are now manifesting new abilities and incorporating cybernetic systems and replacement limbs, hinting at a more sinister force behind the invasion through the world-gates.

To compensate for this growing threat, the members of the Renner Defense League command staff have dusted off old plans from the Project Gigante design competition, the JagdHund, or Hunting Hound. JagdHund was a concept once deemed too large and unwieldy for the battlefield, but it has been recalled to the forefront as the threat literally grows larger.

JagdHund’s paired heavy gatling weapons are capable of dealing with hordes or point targets with equal ease, while the dorsal-mounted main gun, a superheavy maser cannon, is dedicated to frying and boiling the larger monsters emerging through the dimensional breaches. The directed energy weapon is an experiment, and has not been properly developed to withstand the rigors of close-range combat with kaiju. Plans are in the works to add different weapons and countermeasures to the JagdHund arsenal.

The majority of the Hund crews are composed of Quads, or quadruple amputees, wounded veterans and civilian volunteers who have been maimed and disfigured by the invading megafauna. Body modifications are sometimes necessary for final adjustments, but replacement limbs are provided. Quads came about originally from the Assault Raptor program, but have proved to be an invaluable asset in the fight against the invading monsters.

I suggest joining my Patreon at www.patreon.com/johnbearross for a monthly rolling 50% discount on my entire inventory, including this one.

I personally love Warhound Titans and have a full size one printed and painted, though I was never a fan of how the Vulcan Mega Bolters look like a brick with a magazine which would run empty after 5 seconds of continuous fire. This is my attempt to make something more visually striking and with a magazine more suitable for such an immense weapon. The arm mount is sized to other arm mounts which can be found on Cults for free. Just to mix things up a bit, I created a version of the Mega Bolter with twin short barrels and long barrels. The full pack comes with two complete Bolters with short/long barrel along with separate parts for those who want to print separate objects. As always, hope you all enjoy and don't hesitate to contact me with any concerns you may have.

The photographed Bolter is a test print using Nylon 12.

Hey Hey, Been a while hasn't it. I'm back from a long trip in southern Asia so naturally I come back home and open up blender to see if i still got it.

This is a modification for Tersus's Gorkabot (https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/gorkabot). Send the original creator some love. Their work is incredible and part of the reason I got into 3D modelling in the first place.

What have I done? Basically a conversion into the Morkabot variant. But wait there's more! I've fully supported up the model. Which fits comfortably on to just 3 Saturn 2 build plates.

A lot of you have probably downloaded this model and haven't had the time to support it, so here you go. I'm fairly decent at supporting but a bit rusty so there may be some mistakes so make sure to run it through UV tools.

V2 Update
-Magnetized all arm and weapon connection points.
-Added tons of new arm/weapon/Bitz styles
-Fixed a few meshes errors
-Made an attempt to allow the doors to open and pivot.
-Combined meshes to optimize printing in resin.

I have always been a big fan of the stealers of genetics from a popular board game set on a drifting, abandoned hulk in space, especially the early plastic ones with the humped back and ribbed muscles. I first came across them as soul stealers for the now OOP game Space Crusade.

I've also always wanted to do larger, warrior variants, compatible with space bugs from the world's most popular grim-dark tabletop wargame. So I've sculpted one - my first real organic sculpt. Still learning, but this has been a fun project. Fits with standard xenos warrior bits.

This file is only the torso. Pictured bits are for illustrative purposes only.

You can download compatible heads here: https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/soul-stealer-warrior-head-bit

And classic 'Soul Stealer' style arms are available as part of this model: https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/soul-stealer-purestrain-poseable-arms

UPDATE: Had a suggestion of a version with smoother ribbing, so added it as an alternative design.

When building Gore Krusha Mega Walkers, greenskin Meks sometimes opt to build massive klanky klaws as melee weapons instead of the often-seen giant saws.


FOR BEST QUALITY PRINT, PLEASE READ ALL(!) OF BELOW:

This highly detailed Klaw Arm is compatible to my Gore Krusha's Mega Walker
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/gore-krusha-mega-walker

I REALLY recommend a layer high of 0.050 or lower for all parts to get the quality I intended.
Please see the pics of my print, those are all in FDM (0,05mm layer height)!

I tried to keep the need of tree supports low, but I recommend it to use them on some parts - decide for yourself & make sure to set the tree support z-distance to a multiple of 2 (layer height) for optimal removal (keep in mind: layer height 0.05 to 0.075(!) )


----------------------------------------------------------------------
-------------- EXCEPTIONAL 'fings for this model: --------------------
----------------------------------------------------------------------

---------- MOVABLE PARTS ----------
- Most pivot points are actually functional, pose the arm as you want!
- I have included a functional hydraulics option for the klaw, so it can move once assembled.
 -> You need a well calibrated printer to get this hydraulics working. Print all *FlexHydraulics*.stl with wallcount = e.g. 99 to get a massive print without infill.
 -> For the FlexHydraulics pins you need to cut of ca. 10mm of regular 1,75mm filament. (I did not test this in resin, but I guess you could print them)
 -> As an option to the FlexHydraulics there are two fixed versions. Have a look in the parts.
- Print all PINS with wallcount = e.g. 99 to get a massive print without infill.

---------- CABLES and WIRES ----------

KlawArm_03 Bits come with an option to glue in some wires (or filament).
If you use some 0,75mm² or 0,5mm² electrical wires the arm could still be movable :)

---------- Arm on the LEFT or RIGHT? ----------
You can print all parts normally except the shoulder pauldrons. (because of the flat printing side)
-> You have to mirror both pauldrons if you want the arm on the left side of your model (from your point of view)

---------- ASSEMBLY ----------

If you need instructions - just open all files in 3D Builder or e.g. Meshmixer. There you can look where they need to go.

---------- FOLLOWING: ----------

Shame less beggin' for some coins for caffeine I need doin' stuff like that :-)

Please consider a tip ....this highly detailed model was a work of 80h+ of free time!
If you do so, I HIGHLY APPRECIATE YOUR GENEROSITY :-)

Kind regards,
Tersus

Gore Krushas are build by the biggest and craziest meks at the peak of a greenskin WAAAAAGH! as a symbol of their gods - Towering over the battlefield this 'eavy armored walker krushes smaller enemies by simply stomping them to bloody goo (with insane laughter from the Gore Kursha Kaptin').
Meanwhile larger targets can be engaged with it's mega chain choppa, ripping through armor easily.
Although not very accurate, the Gore Krushas ranged weapons have 'nuff shootin' to hit and kill all targets. The sound of high kaliber gattlas at full auto bursts is horrifying or at least intimidating for the most enemies (....or motivating in case of greenskin ears)


FOR BEST QUALITY PRINT, PLEASE READ ALL(!) OF BELOW:

To print the Gore Krusha Mega Walker, you need time or a large resin printer ;-)
I REALLY recommend a layer high of 0.075 or lower for all parts to get the quality I intended.
Please see the pics, those are all printed in FDM (<=0,075mm)!

I tried to keep the need of tree supports low, but I recommend it to use them on some parts - decide for yourself & make sure to set the tree support z-distance to a multiple of 2 (layer hight) for optimal removal (keep in mind: layer hight 0.05 to 0.075(!) )
(The Mega Choppa should be printed with tree support, I included a version with the teef supported, this is also tested)

----------------------------------------------------------------------
-------------- EXCEPTIONAL 'fings for this model: --------------------
----------------------------------------------------------------------

---------- SPIKES ----------

Print them "laying", not standing, or else they will easily snap of if you ram another model ;-)

---------- Exhausts ----------

"GoreKrusha_Exhausts02_Bars_1.75mmFilament.stl" can be combined with "GoreKrusha_Exhausts02.stl" for Resin printers.
In FDM just use some 1.75mm filament & make sure you don't snap of the middle post - trust me :D

---------- LEGS ----------

The legs can be posed standing or walking, but I recommend standing for both to find a good balance for the model.

---------- ARMS ----------

- !!! All joints MUST be printed laying flat !!! This is important, else they will likely snap of due to the weight of the arms.
- The arms should fit thight, but they are not perfect, better glue them after posing
- The ammo belt is a "flexi" print-in-place, once finished, you can gently move the joints to breake it free. With this, the dakka arm can be posed freely as you want.

---------- DA RIGGAZ (Crew) ----------

- Da Riggaz are posed and remixed from https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3985624 by poikilos
- To print Da Riggaz you need tree supports, I flipped them back 15° or 30° (depending on the model) and lifted them +1,5mm on the Z-axies, so the supports will pe printed first. Layer hight 0.05mm, enable support roof with ~0.75mm.

---------- Over all printing recommendation! ----------

- I printed the bottom plate with 25% infill, since it has to carry the weight of the model (about 1,2kg!)
- Many parts have a "flat surface" -> face those to the build plate.
- Detaild sides / most visible sides should be faced towards the cooling fan.

---------- ASSEMBLY ----------

If you need instructions - just open all files in 3D Builder or e.g. Meshmixer. There you can look where they go.


---------- FOLLOWING: ----------

Quite a bit larger than an Imperial Baneblade, a Kill Grinda Mega Fortress is truly a fearsome idol of the brutish Ork gods:
On massive, krushin' trakks, armed with weapons capable of destroying entire hab blocks with one shot, they rumble onwards, where da fORKtress Kaptains points them to.
Only the most powerful Warbosses have 'nuff teef to pay the bestest meks to build these mega-super-heavy assault vehicles.

An IMPORTANT note for the scale :D
- Quote of an imperial agent during a massive Ork encounter on Fungusius Primus:
"Big Mek Gutgrinda once build this thing at a scale of a Baneblade (~79%).... he was KRUSHED and GRINDED brutally to deff by WAAAGHBOSS Gobba Gitkrusha's 'GORKAfORKress' (100% scale)" ;-)



----------------------------------------------------------------------
------- FOR BEST PRINT QUALITY , PLEASE READ ALL(!) OF BELOW: --------
----------------------------------------------------------------------

I REALLY recommend a layer hight of 0.075 or lower for all parts to get the quality I intended.
Please see the pics, those are all printed in FDM (<=0,075mm)!

All parts are printed without tree supports, some parts don't need supports, but please decide for your self. :)

----------------------------------------------------------------------
---------------- EXCEPTIONAL 'fings for this model: ------------------
----------------------------------------------------------------------

---------- Over all printing recommendation! ----------

Many parts have a "flat surface" -> face those to the build plate. Keep in mind, the z-axies does the detailed job!
Detailed sides / most visible sides should be faced towards the cooling fan.

The supa gattla can fit two 5x3mm magnet to be rotatable. The "KillGindaMegaFortress_SupaGattla_Pin.stl" does a similar job, but not as good, I guess... although I never tested the magnets.

The main gun can be assembled in 3 ways:
- Mega Zzappa
- Nukular Shell (with or without spacer, as you like)
- None of both

I printed the supa gattla ammo without a raft, but if you have problems with adhesion, use a raft.
-> If you have concerns about the sharp corners of the ammo belt in FMD, you have the right feeling, but "in the end it doesn't matter", you will not see this issue after assembly.
-> enable "print thin walls" in cura or equivalent in your slicer.

Arrange the lobbas ("KillGrindaMegaFortress_Lobbas02 - 07 & _LazerMarker) as you like, view all files in e.g. 3D Builder or Meshmixer to see how I designed them. The "Lazer sight"-bit is optional, you can replace it with an additional lobba as you like.

---------- Assembly ----------

All parts have a arritation point, so just "move" them until they snap or feel right.
- If you need instructions: just open all files in 3D Builder or e.g. Meshmixer. There you can look where all parts belong to.

Not the best weapon for Smaller Knights, but I am a completionist. This is the last one on my list.

The C-Beamer is a relic weapon usually overlooked because it does more damage the farther away the target is, and less up close, which is a disadvantage on the close-range, terrain-choked tabletops of the current edition.

But, it's free. ;)

Supported versions have a lot of tiny sub-supports that you will want to flick out after curing, especially on barrel 3. It seemed the only way to save that spiraling effect.

You might not be able to access or paint the interior cages of barrels 2 or 3. If that is unacceptable, I recommend barrel 1. It's cleaner and sleeker.

Everything is included from the shoulder socket down.

Ball and socket upper arms are included, in case you want to keep a fixed, glued pose.

I recommend the flat-elbowed upper arms, and magnetizing with an 8mm x 2mm or 8mm x 3mm neodymium magnet glued to the fused upper arm, and steel magnets glued to the elbow "socket" of the weapon.

I usually glue a steel BB in the socket, then cap it with a pair of glued-on steel washers. See pics for reference.

You'll lose some poseability, but gain modularity.

Also, check out my other mech and knight parts, most of which are free.
https://cults3d.com/en/users/johnbearross/creations

Enjoy!

Best,
JBR

Want to fire some flesh eatin' short range artillery ammunishun that's not a bug?? Rukka Buggys are your vehicle of choice! Slap it! Expolode it!
"How much bity or 'splodin' flesh balls you want to shoot??" - "Yes."


FOR BEST QUALITY PRINT, PLEASE READ ALL(!) OF BELOW:

To print the Rukka Buggy, you need time or a resin printer ;-)
I REALLY recommend a layer high of 0.075mm or lower for all parts to get the quality I intended.
Please see the pics, those are all printed in FDM (<=0,075mm)!

I highly recommend it to use tree supports (at least on the crew) - make sure to set the tree support z-distance to a multiple of 2 (layer hight) for optimal removal (keep in mind: layer hight 0.05 (crew) or 0.075mm (buggy))

---------- Over all printing recommendation (FDM) ----------

- Many parts have a flat surface -> face those to the build plate. Print slow (25mm/s)
- Detaild sides / most visible sides should be faced towards the cooling fan.
- Crew should be printed with tree supports, rotated 45° back (so the face is up). Support Z-distance should be a multiple of 2 to 3 of the layer hight (0.05 - 0.075mm). PRINT SLOW - Outer wall max 25mm/s. You want dem details gooood!

The most difficult parts (actually not the Gobbo Crew...):
- "RuckaBuggy_Rear_02.stl": you need to be super carefull to remove tree supports (they are needed). My test print broke on the bars while removing them. I was able to glue it back on (tip: smooth cracks with a lighter)
- "RuckaBuggy_Front_04.stl": failed 4 times while removing tree supports, combined with other parts. I needed to print this part as a single part with normal supports.

---------- Assembly ----------

If you need instructions - just open all files in 3D Builder or e.g. Meshmixer. There you can look where they go.
Some parts are press fits (e.g. the wheels) you don't need to glue them, unless you print in resin (not tested).
I recommend to "dry fit" the parts with blu tack or a similar reusable putty.


---------- FOLLOWING: ----------

Shame less beggin' for => "Tossin' a coin to your Tersus...." :D

Please consider a tip ....this highly detailed model was a work of many hours of free time!
If you do so, I HIGHLY APPRECIATE YOUR GENEROSITY :-) :-) :-)

Kind regards,
Tersus

----------------------------

With the mysterious Dark Powers making their once-hidden presence more known, new, sinister mech designs have begun to appear on the battlefields of the Junctionworld inter-reality gate networks.

Notable among these new nightmares is a tailed, tentacled monstrosity labeled by intel operatives at the Mercenary Guild as Project Abby.

These warped, spiked, and twisted armors are malevolent in form and purpose. They have a heat cannon on one arm as their primary ranged weapon, while the melee component of their arsenal is composed of an energized whip weapon system. Crackling with plasma, this cluster of mechanical tentacles can be used to impale, crush, or slice through enemy targets. The Abby features a tail-like appendage that performs the same function, protecting the armored walker from the rear.

Project Abby mechs also seem to be nesting grounds for ScytheBots, verminous robot drones that seem to claim the dreaded hulks as mobile nests. These hive-like bots provide a symbiotic layer of protection for the mech, cutting down infantry that venture too close.

The Gorkabot is a massive armored mech, built as an effigy of a greenskin god! Armed to da teef da Gorkabot krushes all kind of ememys with it's klaw while shredding infantry with hails of bullets from the DAKKA-Storm gun.


In the Gorkabots belly is space for a few greenskins to pop out, if the time is good for some krumpin'!








FOR BEST QUALITY PRINT, PLEASE READ ALL(!) OF BELOW:





To print the Gorkabot, you need time or a resin printer ;-)


I REALLY recommend a layer high of 0.075 or lower for all parts to get the quality I intended.


Please see the pics, those are all printed in FDM (<=0,075mm)!





I tried to keep the need of tree supports low, but I highly recommend it to use them - make sure to set the tree support z-distance to a multiple of 2 (layer hight) for optimal removal (keep in mind: layer hight 0.05 to 0.075(!) )








----------------------------------------------------------------------


-------- EXCEPTIONAL 'fings for this model: ----------


----------------------------------------------------------------------








---------- COMPATIBILITY ----------





Arms and legs should be compatible to my Mega Bots (not testet)





---------- MAIN BODY ----------





"GorkaBot_Belly.stl" prints without tree support! Just use regular supports.


"GorkaBot_Torso.stl" prints without tree support! Just use regular supports. flip the model slightly to the back (see Cura screenshot)


The doors should be printed without supports with a brim (see Cura screenshot)





---------- LEGS ----------





The legs are unique, there is an individual model for the right / left leg. Those are mirrorable / interchangeable if you want.





---------- ARMS----------





The arms should fit 10x4mm magnets (not tested) but also have a ball joint for more posability...





The "GorkaBot_Klaw_Arm_02.stl" should be printed 45° "floating 1,5mm in the air" see my Cura screenshot - this will give you the best quality result!





---------- Over all printing recommendation! ----------





Many parts have a "flat surface" -> face those to the build plate.


Detaild sides / most visible sides should be faced towards the cooling fan.





---------- Assembly ----------





if you need instructions - just open all files in 3D Builder or e.g. Meshmixer. There you can look where they go








---------- FOLLOWING: ----------





Shame less beggin' for some coins for coffein I need doin' stuff like that :-D ;-)





Please consider a tip ....this highly detailed model was a work of 100h+ of free time!


If you do so, I HIGHLY APPRECIATE YOUR GENEROSITY :-) :-) :-)





Kind regards,


Tersus

This is a shoulder/carapace mounted Turbolaser Destructor (twin turbolaser) for use with Stroganoff's Battleduke Warstrider model.

It's a mashup of this Apocalypse Rocket Launcher by totenpf:
https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4814519
...the turbolaser barrels from this Wardog:
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/lucius-wardog-titan
...and part of the Laser Blaster model that comes with the Battleduke
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/epic-scale-mars-warlord-titan

I took all the bits, chopped them around, scaled them to fit and mashed them together.

It should fit exactly onto the Battleduke model if you print them both at the same scale. If you want to use it with an AT-scale model you'll need to scale it up a bit; probably about 125% but I don't know exactly as I haven't tried it and I don't currently have any AT models to measure.

The model is slightly asymmetrical. I think it works better on the right shoulder; mirror it for the left.

The Skrappin' Mega Bot is a stompin' armored Mech capable of moving objects without any efforts using it's powerfull trakktor kannon! Dead 'ard

killy saws tear apart every enemy getting to close. Once the Skrappin' Mega Bot krushed some enemy vehicles, turing those into piles of skrapp, it 

can do some quick n' dirty fixin' jobs on allied vehicles or mechs.


FOR BEST QUALITY PRINT, PLEASE READ ALL(!) OF BELOW:

Beneath my Krumpin' Mega Bot this is one of my most detailed models until now!

To print this monster, you need time or a resin printer ;-)
I REALLY recommend a layer high of 0.075 or lower for all parts to get the quality I intended, while designing this model - please see the pics, those

are printed in FDM (<=0,075mm)!

I tried to keep the need of tree supports low, but I highly recommend it to use them - make sure to set the tree support z-distance to a multiple of 2

(layer hight) for optimal removal (keep in mind: layer hight 0.05 to 0.075(!) )

For a few bitz I added a resin version with "_Resin" in the file name - unlike the FDM versions those don't have a flat bottom. (I have not test printed 

these files, but they should be good to go!)

The Trakktor Kannon can be a variant of an actuall (rattling) Kannon, as it lifts up 'eavy objects and throw them with a high velocity to enemy gitz - 

less explosiv, more smashin' - same damage! ;-)

----------------------------------------------------------------------
---------- EXCEPTIONAL 'fings for this model: ----------
----------------------------------------------------------------------


---------- COMPATIBILITY ----------

Most parts are compatible to my Krumpin' Mega Bot, so you can build your variant as you like :)
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/krumpin-mega-bot

---------- MAIN BODY ----------

You CAN use two 10x4mm Neodym magnets for the junction "hip <> main hull" to get a rotatable/removable body!
As an alternative to the magnets print the file "ScrappinMegaBot_Hip02.stl"

---------- LEGS ----------

The legs are unique, there is a individual model for the right / left leg. Those are mirrorable / interchangeable if you want.

---------- Over all printing recommendation! ----------

Many parts have a "flat surface" - face those to the build plate.

---------- FOLLOWING: ----------

Shame less beggin' for some coins for coffein I need doin' stuff like that :-D ;-)

Please consider a tip ....this HIGH detailed model was a work of 80h+ of free time!
This model is not a simple remix, all parts of my Krumpin' Mega Bot have been reviewed and altered with new details! :-)
If you do so, I HIGHLY APPRECIATE YOUR GENEROSITY :-) :-):-)

Kind regards,
Tersus

Designed up this dealer button to use in home games or have just as something laying around for any poker fan. It was inspired by a dealer button in Pokerstars VR.

Printing:

Ring - Infil to add weight, supports needed for spade inset. Letter embossing doesn't need it.
Spade - Infil to add weight, no supports
Letters - Print flat, already scaled to fit nicely in the embossing
Star - Infil to add weight.

Full print with 4x4x4 walls/top/bottom and 38% infil came to about 48g in weight.

Glue in lettering and spade. Star may need minor sanding but should push fit into the space tightly and not need anything else to secure it.

I want to thank you folks for helping me reach 500 followers after only a month of paid sales.

As a token of appreciation, here's the RFBC-500 Avtomat Pushka (sorry, my computer-translated Russian is terrible), an Automatic Rifle Cannon (RFBC proxy).

It's available in both Right (A) and Left (B) versions, with the main weapon body having a choice of stick or drum magazine.

Also, one of my heavy stubby gatlings is incorporated into the design. That asymmetric part of the design is a nice feature, in my opinion.

A pair of weapon arms, long and short, are supplied, as well as upper arms at a variety of angles for magnetization.

I glue the ball and sockets together, then glue 12mm x 2mm magnets to the bottom of the upper arm.

An 8mm x 2mm magnet will fit in the face of the main weapon body. I usually glue in washers in the barrel section. 4mm inner diameter/9mm outer diameter washers usually do it, or #6 washers. Or just glue them together and print more.

You can use opposing magnets in the weapon arms (remember opposite poles) to the new upper arms. I recommend 12mm x 3mm magnets.

Enjoy, and thanks again! More good stuff to come.

Best,
JBR

P.S. Check out my other Knight parts, most of which are free.
https://cults3d.com/en/users/johnbearross/creations

P.P.S. I started a Discord server for feedback and for folks to follow progress of my sculpts.
https://discord.gg/NJtm78rF63

P.P.P.S. I have updated the upper arms to ensure compatibility with Project Quixote, my new modular mech kit. Check it out.

https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/project-quixote-28mm-dieselpunk-modular-pre-supported-mech-kit

Best,
JBR

The Krumpin' Mega Bot is a hulking, heavily armored monster! Pistons, welded to powerful close combat weapons, such as the Ripper Klaw deliver enormous hydraulik power to every git or vehicle gettin' to close.
Other than the more commonly Deff Bots and or Kans, Krumpin' Mega Bots are usually armed with high speed rattling weapons of high calibers to kill enemies even before reaching them in close combat! (Or just to make horrible loud noise...)

EDIT: Most Parts are compatible to my Skrappin' Mega Bot
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/skrappin-mega-bot
Build your Bot as you like! :-)

FOR BEST QUALITY PRINT, PLEASE READ ALL(!) OF BELOW:

This is my ambitious model until now!

To print this monster, you need time or a resin printer ;-)
I REALLY recommend a layer high of 0.075 or better for all parts to get the quality I intended, while designing this model - please see the pics, those are printed in FDM

(<=0,075mm)!

I tried to keep the need of tree supports low, but I highly recommend it to use tree supports - make sure to set the tree support z-distance to a multiple of 2 for optimal removal

(keep in mind: layer hight 0.05 to 0.075(!) )

For the Rippa Klaw I added a resin version with "_Resin" in the file name - unlike the FDM versions those don't have a flat bottom. (I have not test printed these files, but they

should be good to go!)

----------------------------------------------------------------------
---------- EXCEPTIONAL 'fings for this model: ----------
----------------------------------------------------------------------


---------- GUN ARM: ----------

THE RATTLA KANNON MAGAZINE IS ROTATABLE IF DONE AS INTENDED!!

For the axies you simply insert usual filament!
If you don't glue the "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_06.stl" to "...05.stl" the "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Mag.stl" is interchangeable - who knows what might be released in future...... ;-)
-> If you don't want this or don't have filament, just glue the parts as wanted.


Assembly as followed: (please see also the last two pics/screenshots!

1. Stick (NOT glue, if you want it to be removable) together:
"MegaBot_RattlerKannon_05" & "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_06", OPTIONAL: "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Barrel.stl"

2. Insert a 1.75mm filament (42mm long - as the answer to all questions, lol) into "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Mag_Back_Spacer.stl", large side first, followed by

"MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Mag".

2.a) Glue on all parts of "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Mag_Back.stl", if you want more realistic details (even if Ork xD).
2.a.note: Warning: print "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Mag_Back.stl" with "brim" 3mm+.
They will, regardless of brim width, fall apart after removing the brim. This is intended so you can glue them bitz more random on the Mag!

3. "Dry fit" (NO glue at first!) all parts

3.a) View the last two pics (Tinkercad screenshots)!

3.b) "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Trigger.stl" to
 "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Mag_Back_Spacer.stl"

3.c) I recommend to glue in "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_TriggerPin.stl" to "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Trigger.stl" first.

3.d) Glue the filament between "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Trigger.stl" & "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Mag_Back_Spacer.stl"


---------- MAIN BODY ----------

You CAN use two 10x4mm Neodym magnets for the junction "hip <> main hull" to get a rotatable/removable body!

---------- LEGS ----------

The legs are unique, there is a individual model for right / left leg. Those are mirrorable / interchangeable.

---------- Over all printing recommendation! ----------

Many parts have a "flat surface" - face those to the build plate.


---------- FOLLOWING: ----------

Shame less beggin' for some coins for coffein I need doin' stuff like that :-D ;-)

Please consider a tip ....this HIGH detailed model was a work of 100h+ of free time (~50 RL days)! If you do so, I HIGHLY APPRECIATE YOUR GENEROSITY :-) :-):-)

Kind regards,
Tersus

This is probably a first version, I'm currently working on V2 with more details and added a magnet hole, for swappable heads. V1 is usable but there's bits I'm going to clean up, particularly where the ears join the head, but that's for the future. If you don't like it it'll be quick to green stuff.

Any comments are welcome as I rework it.

I decided to include a SLA pre-supported version mostly because I had it, it printed fine for me. Pre suported is hollowed, but over supported leave some marks v2 coming at some point maybe.

Hail, Fellow Scions!

The standard Thermal Cannon that comes from the factory is nice, but I wanted a little bit more.

This matches my alternate carapace gun from my other designs.

I magnetize my Knights at the elbow. There's is a socket there for whatever method you prefer. There are two parts...

The gunshield slips over the two barrels of the cannon, and should be glued. Some fitting may be required, depending on your printer.

Based around the internal structure of Stroganoff's excellent 4th Planet Battleduke 

https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/various/4th-planet-battleduke-pre-olympian-god-stroganoff

All armor plating and pattern specific components of this model are modeled from scratch in XSI Softimage.
Intended to be used in small scale gaming so all tolerances are set for that scale, final model should stand roughly 5.5 inches tall. If you want to use it for the more popular scale of grimdark gaming you can scale it up by 363.5% but I cant guarantee any of the tolerances will work.

https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/6-8mm-extra-accessories-lucifer-pattern-overlord-goliath-warmech

Some armor plates include BLNK and V01/02 versions, these are variant pieces that have slight cosmetic differences to help customize your prints.

Includes ready made ports for magnetizing arm and shoulder weapon options, allowing you to swap weapon loadouts as you wish. Accepts 2x standard 3mm×8mm disc magnet in the body and a 6×32 machine nut in each weapon, both are available at most hardware stores

Should not be printed to replace pre-existing miniatures options, please support the original manufacturer

Re-scale and remix of Jimzbeanz Power Fist to suit the 2018 Version of Adeptus Titanicus, with Upper Arm components rescaled from Strogs 40k Version. Added the magnet well so it can easily be used with the Plastic kits. Designed to print on DLP printers.

EDIT 12/01/2020 - I went to print this today and noticed I hadn't seated the mounting ring for the magnet correctly in the upper arm. Uploaded the fixed Version 2 file.

EDIT 19/01/2020 - I did a test print and the fist itself is a bit too large when compared to an AT18 Warlord Titan. I will work on the re-scaling and test this probably tomorrow since i have the day off. It is for now perfectly scaled to suit 28mm Knights, which is kind of cool/funny.

EDIT 17/03/2020 - So after some feedback the following files itself need to be scaled to 80% - Palm_WithFingers, Thumb_Complete and Palm_Gun. The Elbow_Joint needs to be scaled to 90%. This will give a much closer scaling to the Plastic version and won't look as oversized.

This is inspired by the original Kev Adams 1990's era gargant with the rounded belly and arm and shoulder weapons.

some of the notable changes I made to the original design was the placement of the feed, rather than underneath they are to either side of the body, Another change was how I mounted the Buzz saw, I wanted it to look like it had a greater range of movement the 3d change was to the belly gun mount the original left huge holes in the belly that could be seen through during games, so I have added a big mantlet that I think gives the gargant a more solid look.

Also a minor tweak i widened the balcony on the back so now you can add infantry models there, but if you intend to do this do it before gluing the top body to the mid body.
With the modificatiosn its a little wider than the old model, and best mounted on a games workshop 80mm or reaper miniatures 75mm base. I have included a simple printable base id you don't have either of these sizes to hand

theoreticly you could scale this up for Titanicus, you would need to print at about 150%, priniting full size for 40k may be 2 difficult unless you cut up the hull parts or happen to have a huge print bed


You can add extra weapons from this selection here, Please mesage me if i have forgotten a weapon, i think i added all of them.
